Nit: you can leverage early returns to reduce nesting:

```python
        if is_dataclass(o):
            return asdict(o)
        if isinstance(o, collections.abc.Mapping):
            return dict(o)
        if isinstance(o, collections.abc.Sequence):
            return list(o)
        if isinstance(o, self.safe_to_str_types):
            return str(o)
        try:
            return super().default(o)
        except TypeError:
            # punt and just try str()
            # TODO: can we find a better strategy here?
            return str(o)
```

While not required, that style is encouraged: https://www.pantsbuild.org/docs/style-guide#prefer-early-returns-in-functions.

