Talked to @jamesls and @joguSD offline about this. I think it is fine to put it on the service model under the argument that valid transformations of the service id is an extension of the service model. However, the name of these transformations should not be client specific. We talked about this idea as well, but I would be fine with setting the `ServiceModel.service_id` to a class like this that subclasses from `str`:
```python
class ServiceID(str):
    def hyphenize(self):
        return self.replace(' ', '-').lower()
```
The nice part about making a separate ServiceID object is that we will not have to bloat the `ServiceModel` class with properties like `hyphened_service_id` as right now there are five different accepted ways the service id can be represented. So if we ever needed a new one, we can just add a method to this object. Also we will not have to pollute a lot of the modules with the current `get_service_event_name` import from the `utils` module. Thoughts?

