Let's change this to `_isAvailable` like the other dashboards, but then we should also update _maybeInitializeDashboard which reads the value in two places:

- Observer registration up on line 437 should change to the following https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/blob/678e6b90e0341c26691441a77c09223708012037/tensorboard/plugins/profile/tf_profile_dashboard/tf-profile-dashboard.html#L437
```javascript
_maybeInitializeDashboard(_isAttached, _isAvailable)
````

- Observer definition down on line 487 should change to the following https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/blob/678e6b90e0341c26691441a77c09223708012037/tensorboard/plugins/profile/tf_profile_dashboard/tf-profile-dashboard.html#L487-L492

```javascript
_maybeInitializeDashboard: function(isAttached, isAvailable) {
  if (this._initialized || !isAttached || !isAvailable) {
    // Either this dashboard is already initialized ... or we are not yet
    // ready to initialize.
    return;
