DuaManager needs to know if DUA is removed or added or changed. 
One way I can think of is like this:

```c++
// before update Child addresses
bool oldHasDua = aChild.GetDomainUnicastAddress() != nullptr;
// After update Child addresses
Get<DuaManager>().UpdateChildDomainUnicastAddress(aChild, oldHasDua);
```

We can then find for the new Dua in `UpdateChildDomainUnicastAddress` itself. 
So we can minimize changes to `MleRouter` by only collecting the minimal information we need before updating Child addresses and pass it to `DuaManager` for further logic.

